http.title: Norfolk Electronic Library PC Booking System
http.html:
Contact us | Privacy and cookies

Welcome to Norfolk Electronic Library Online PC Booking Service.

We have public computer terminals available for booking in all of our libraries. The standard session length is 120 minutes.

Computer usage is subject to Norfolk County Council's terms and conditions. If you have no special requirements about which PC you use, you can book the next available computer in any library here

A system to allow self-service customer access, called Open Libraries, has been installed at a number of libraries. At some times during the week, there will be no staff present in the libraries, you will need to be specially registered in orde to be able to gain access to the library during these periods. Please contact your library for more information or find out how to register for Open Libraries here.

We reserve the right to change, amend or cancel your bookings.

Please note that if you are more than 10 minutes late logging on, your booking will automatically be cancelled and the PC will become available for use by other customers.

If you encounter any problems please telephone the Customer Service Centre Number on 0344 800 8020 Monday - Friday 9.00am to 5.00pm, or email information@norfolk.gov.uk
